<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 09 at 3:41PM EST  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...SNOW WILL CAUSE SLIPPERY TRAVEL LATE THIS AFTERNOON AND
EVENING...
Snow will continue late this afternoon and early evening mainly near
and south of a line from Grand Haven to Grand Rapids and Eaton
Rapids. This includes I-96 especially west of Ionia, I-94 especially
west of Albion and I-196.
Snow will limit visibilities to below a half mile at times and snow
rates will be such that roads will become snow covered and slippery
as well. Roads may develop some icy spots where snow has fallen due
to temperatures falling below the freezing mark.
If traveling across the southwest corner of Lower Michigan late
this afternoon and evening be prepared to encounter snow covered and
slick roads. You will need to allow some extra time to reach your
destination as conditions may dictate that you need to slow down.</description>
